@startuml
title KiTicket — reservation and sandbox-payment flow
actor Customer
participant "React client" as Web
participant "NestJS API" as API
database PostgreSQL as DB
collections Redis
queue RabbitMQ as MQ

Customer -> Web : select event and seats
Web -> API : POST /waiting-room/{eventId}/join
API -> Redis : INCR waiting:event:{eventId}:sequence
API -> DB : save waiting-room entry
API --> Web : entry / admission token

Web -> API : POST /reservations\n(admission token, seat IDs)
API -> DB : validate event, venue seats and pricing
API -> Redis : atomically acquire all seat locks
API -> DB : transaction: save pending reservation\nand locked ReservationSeat rows
API -> MQ : publish reservation.created
API --> Web : pending reservation and expiry

Web -> API : POST /payments\n(idempotency key)
API -> DB : save or return pending payment
API --> Web : payment
Web -> API : POST /payments/{id}/complete\n(sandbox outcome)
API -> DB : transaction: confirm/book/create tickets\nor cancel/expire/remove locked seats
API -> Redis : release owner-held locks
API -> MQ : publish payment/ticket event
API --> Web : payment, reservation and tickets
@enduml

